                <!-- Main content -->
                <div class="internal">
                    <h3 class="main_text" style="margin: 50px; text-align: center;">The Problem</h3>
                    <p class="main_text">"All By Our shelf" started with the need for more efficient display 
                    and storage requirements. We look for small problems in our daily lives that might be solved with 
                    current technology, one of which is that our team members need to show off their growing collection of figures. 
                    He was running out of space and wanted a new way to show it. While this may seem like a trivial issue,
                    it's a necessity for anyone who wants to show or just keep something in a safe space.
                    Current shelves are limited in flexibility - items placed in the back are blocked by items placed in the front, 
                    for example, and are not easily accessible or displayed.<br><br><br><br><br></p>
                    <h3 class="main_text" style="margin: 50px; text-align: center;">Our Solution</h3>
                    <p class="main_text">We proposed a shelf with greater display 
                    and storage flexibility that can be controlled wirelessly via a 
                    bluetooth application on the user's phone. Each row of the shelf is made 
                    up of two parts, a front and back and the two will be separated. 
                    This allows, different categories of items to be displayed or stored.
                    Through the app, users can switch back and forth between the two 
                    sections, so that items on the shelves can be placed in two different 
                    ways. To this end, we will design a rack so that the two parts can 
                    be connected on an axis and rotated so as to switch. Each line of the 
                    bookshelf will change independently.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Footer -->
